{"data":{"allPostTitles":{"edges":[{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/accessibility/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/annotations/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/axis/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/getting-started/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/internationalization/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/linear-gauge-appearance/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/linear-gauge-dimensions/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/pointers/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/ranges/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/user-interaction/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}}]},"postBySlug":{"html":"<h1 id=\"internationalization\"><a href=\"#internationalization\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Internationalization</h1>\n<p>Linear gauge provide supports for internationalization for below gauge elements.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Axis label</li>\n<li>Tooltip</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For more information about number and date formatter you can refer <code class=\"language-text\">internationalization</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"globalization\"><a href=\"#globalization\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Globalization</h2>\n<p>Globalization is the process of designing and developing an component that works in different cultures/locales. Internationalization library is used to globalize number in Linear Gauge component using <code class=\"language-text\">LoadCldrData</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">SetCulture</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">SetCurrencyCode</code> methods.</p>\n<h3 id=\"numeric-format\"><a href=\"#numeric-format\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Numeric Format</h3>\n<p>In the below example axis labels are <code class=\"language-text\">globalized</code> to EUR.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">EjsLinearGauge</span> Width <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"650px\"</span> Height <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"300px\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugeLabel</span> Format<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"c\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeFontSettings<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugeFont</span> Color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"red\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeFont<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeFontSettings<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeLabel<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n\n@code <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Inject</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">protected</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">IJSRuntime</span> JsRuntime <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">get</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">set</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">protected</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">override</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">OnAfterRender</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>JsRuntime<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Ejs</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">LoadCldrData</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token string\">\"ca-gregorian.json\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token string\">\"currencies.json\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token string\">\"numbers.json\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token string\">\"timeZoneNames.json\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">SetCulture</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"de\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">SetCurrencyCode</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"EUR\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/linear-gauge/images/numeric-format.png\" alt=\"Linear Gauge with Internationalization Sample\"></p>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"Internationalization Linear gauge provide supports for internationalization for below gauge elements. Axis label Tooltip For moreâ€¦","fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/internationalization/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/internationalization/","previous":{"html":"<h1 id=\"appearance\"><a href=\"#appearance\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Appearance</h1>\n<h2 id=\"linear-gauge-area-customization\"><a href=\"#linear-gauge-area-customization\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Linear Gauge Area Customization</h2>\n<h3 id=\"customize-the-linear-gauge-background\"><a href=\"#customize-the-linear-gauge-background\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Customize the Linear Gauge background</h3>\n<p>Using <code class=\"language-text\">Background</code> property and <code class=\"language-text\">LinearGaugeBorder</code> tag, you can change the background color and border of the Linear Gauge.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">EjsLinearGauge</span> Width <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"200px\"</span> Height <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"400px\"</span> Background<span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"skyblue\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugeBorder</span> Color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"#FF0000\"</span> Width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"2\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeBorder<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/linear-gauge/images/background.png\" alt=\"Linear Gauge with Background Sample\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"linear-gauge-container\"><a href=\"#linear-gauge-container\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Linear Gauge Container</h2>\n<p>The area used to render the ranges and pointers at the center position of the gauge is called <code class=\"language-text\">Container</code>. It can be customized by using <code class=\"language-text\">Type</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">Offset</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">Width</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">Height</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">BackgroundColor</code> properties in <code class=\"language-text\">LinearGaugeContainer</code>. It is of three types namely,</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Normal</li>\n<li>Rounded Rectangle</li>\n<li>Thermometer</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"normal\"><a href=\"#normal\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Normal</h3>\n<p>The normal type will render the container as rectangle and this is the default container type.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugeContainer</span> Width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"30\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugePointers<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugePointer</span> Value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"50\"</span> Width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"15\"</span> Type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Point.Bar\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugePointer<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugePointers<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeContainer<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/linear-gauge/images/bar.png\" alt=\"Linear Gauge with Container\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"rounded-rectangle\"><a href=\"#rounded-rectangle\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Rounded Rectangle</h3>\n<p>The rounded rectangle type will render the container as rectangle with rounded corners.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugeContainer</span> Width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"30\"</span> Type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"ContainerType.RoundedRectangle\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugePointers<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugePointer</span> Value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"50\"</span> Width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"15\"</span> Type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Point.Bar\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugePointer<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugePointers<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeContainer<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/linear-gauge/images/rectangle.png\" alt=\"Linear Gauge with Rounded Rectangle Container\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"thermometer\"><a href=\"#thermometer\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Thermometer</h3>\n<p>This type is used to render the container similar to the thermometer appearance.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugeContainer</span> Width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"30\"</span> Type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"ContainerType.Thermometer\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugePointers<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugePointer</span> Value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"80\"</span> Width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"15\"</span> Type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Point.Bar\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugePointer<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugePointers<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeContainer<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/linear-gauge/images/meter.png\" alt=\"Linear Gauge with Thermometer container\"></p>","id":"705f2319-0586-5778-9244-a3e5ea4bcf32","fields":{"slug":"/linear-gauge/linear-gauge-appearance/","parentPath":"linear-gauge","childPath":"linear-gauge-appearance","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4","header":"<div id=\"doc-right-toc\"><span>Contents</span>\n<ul>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h2\"><a href=\"#linear-gauge-area-customization\">Linear Gauge Area Customization</a></li>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h3\"><a href=\"#customize-the-linear-gauge-background\">Customize the Linear Gauge background</a></li>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h2\"><a href=\"#linear-gauge-container\">Linear Gauge Container</a></li>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h3\"><a href=\"#normal\">Normal</a></li>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h3\"><a href=\"#rounded-rectangle\">Rounded Rectangle</a></li>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h3\"><a href=\"#thermometer\">Thermometer</a></li>\n</ul></div>","breadCrumb":"Linear Gauge/","isReleaseNotes":false,"title":"Blazor [Preview]  component - Syncfusion","description":"Checkout and learn about getting started with Blazor [Preview]  component of Syncfusion Essential JS 2, and more details.","platform":"Blazor [Preview]","isRobots":true}},"next":{"html":"<h1 id=\"getting-started\"><a href=\"#getting-started\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Getting Started</h1>\n<p>This section briefly explains how to include a Linear Gauge in your Blazor client-side application. Refer to this <a href=\"https://ej2.syncfusion.com/blazor/documentation/getting-started/vs-blazor/\">Getting Started with Syncfusion Blazor for Client-Side in Visual Studio 2019 Preview</a> documentation for the introduction and configuring the common specifications.</p>\n<h2 id=\"importing-syncfusion-blazor-component-in-an-application\"><a href=\"#importing-syncfusion-blazor-component-in-an-application\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Importing Syncfusion Blazor component in an application</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Install Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor NuGet package in application using the NuGet Package Manager. Make sure to check the <strong>Include prerelease</strong> option.</li>\n<li>Add the client-side resources through CDN in the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;head&gt;</code> element of the <code class=\"language-text\">~/wwwroot/index.html</code> page.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>head<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>environment include<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Development\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>script src<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"https://cdn.syncfusion.com/ej2/{:version:}/dist/ej2.min.js\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>script<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n     <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>environment<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>head<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"adding-component-package-to-an-application\"><a href=\"#adding-component-package-to-an-application\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Adding component package to an application</h2>\n<p>Open the <strong>~/_Imports.razor</strong> file and import the <code class=\"language-text\">Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGauge</code> package.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\">@<span class=\"token keyword\">using</span> Syncfusion<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>EJ2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Blazor\n@<span class=\"token keyword\">using</span> Syncfusion<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>EJ2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Blazor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>LinearGauge</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"adding-linear-gauge-component-to-an-application\"><a href=\"#adding-linear-gauge-component-to-an-application\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Adding Linear Gauge component to an application</h2>\n<p>Now, add the Syncfusion Blazor Linear Gauge component in any web page razor in the Pages folder. For example, the Linear Gauge component is added to the ~/Pages/ Index.razor page.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"run-the-application\"><a href=\"#run-the-application\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Run the application</h2>\n<p>After the successful compilation of your application,  press F5 to run the application. The Blazor Linear Gauge component will be rendered in the web browser as illustrated in the following screenshot.</p>\n<p>   <img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/linear-gauge/images/pixel.png\" alt=\"Linear Gauge Sample\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"set-pointer-value\"><a href=\"#set-pointer-value\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Set pointer value</h2>\n<p>You can change the pointer value in the following sample using the <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGauge.LinearGaugePointer~_value.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">Value</code></a> property in the <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGauge.LinearGaugePointer_members.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">LinearGaugePointer</code></a> tag.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In Linear Gauge, you can configure multiple axes. On each axis you can add a pointer.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\">@<span class=\"token keyword\">using</span> Syncfusion<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>EJ2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Blazor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>LinearGauge\n\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugePointers<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugePointer</span> Value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"40\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugePointer<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugePointers<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/linear-gauge/images/getting-pointers.png\" alt=\"Linear Gauge with pointer value\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"add-linear-gauge-title\"><a href=\"#add-linear-gauge-title\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Add Linear Gauge title</h2>\n<p>You can add title to the linear gauge using <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGauge.EjsLinearGauge~Title.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">Title</code></a> property and you can customize this title using following properties.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGauge.LinearGaugeTitleStyle_members.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">LinearGaugeTitleStyle</code></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/cref_files/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGaugeFontSettings~Color.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">Color</code></a> - Specifies the title text color</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/cref_files/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGaugeFontSettings~FontStyle.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">FontStyle</code></a> - Specifies font style for the title</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/cref_files/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGaugeFontSettings~FontWeight.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">FontWeight</code></a> - Specifies font weight for the title</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/cref_files/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGaugeFontSettings~Size.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">Size</code></a> - Specifies font size for the title</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/cref_files/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGaugeFontSettings~Opacity.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">Opacity</code></a> - Specifies font opacity for the title</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/cref_files/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGaugeFontSettings~FontFamily.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">FontFamily</code></a> - Specifies font family for the title</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\">@<span class=\"token keyword\">using</span> Syncfusion<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>EJ2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Blazor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>LinearGauge\n\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">EjsLinearGauge</span> Title<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Speed calculator\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugeTitleStyle</span> Color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"blue\"</span>\n                           FontStyle<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"italic\"</span>\n                           FontWeight<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"bold\"</span>\n                           Size<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"15px\"</span>\n                           Opacity<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"0.8\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeTitleStyle<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>LinearGaugePointers<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">LinearGaugePointer</span> Value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"40\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n                <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugePointer<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugePointers<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxis<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>LinearGaugeAxes<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsLinearGauge<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/linear-gauge/images/linear-gauge-title.png\" alt=\"Linear gauge with title\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"add-axis-ranges\"><a href=\"#add-axis-ranges\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Add axis ranges</h2>\n<p>You can categorize the axis values using the <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGauge.LinearGaugeRange~Start.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">Start</code></a> and <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGauge.LinearGaugeRange~End.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">End</code></a> properties in the <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.LinearGauge.LinearGaugeRange_members.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">LinearGaugeRange</code></a>. You can add any number of ranges for an axis using <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Sy